feedback: There were a few mistakes, but they followed what I was asking for the most part. CRS2 did not.

I thought CRS 1 had an easier time understanding me. I also liked that it gave a longer list and was able to narrow it down. CRS2 kept getting confused so I felt it wasn't very helpful in my task in getting a movie recommendation.

CRS 1 had errors or was cyclical, but it at least understood my original prompt and gave me answers relevant to it. Nothing CRS 2 provided was related to my original prompt and some responses were non-sensical.
Neither of these were actually very helpful, I was trying to get more details but it just kept repeating stuff, or not understanding the context. So It didn't seem particularly useful.

Both chatbots did not understand my prompts. They made bad recommendations, e.g. 'choose anything between'.  CRS1 explicitly  ignored one of my questions. Neither gave a reason for their recommendations.

crs 1 remembered the conversation and was mostly able to follow what i asked. did not understand about death in a movie. crs 2 hardly made any sense and could not understand what I was typing. thank you for an interesting study.

CRS 1 did not address my request at all correctly.  When I asked for British comedy recommendations, it said it wasn't a big fan of that and it prefers history.  I tried to coach it to give proper responses but the recommendations it did give didn't meet the criteria at all (e.g. Mrs. Doubtfire, which is a U.S. movie not British).  CRS2 gave much better responses.  It made  few mistakes, like giving me a Monty Python suggestion and "A Fish Called Wanda" when I had clearly said I'd already seen those and wanted other movies, but after I indicated that, it removed them from the list and gave me a list which for the most part was appropriate.  It also gave me a list of such movies from the 1970s specifically when I asked for that (British comedies), with just a few errors. However, then I persisted in correcting further, it lost track of what it was doing and gave me a few short lists that had nothing to do with what I requested.  But overall, it was certainly far better than CRS1, which was pretty much useless in addressing my request.
